    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1071.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department requests that you kindly send to
                    the United States war vessel now stationed in Dominican waters, orders to convey
                    a commission of Dominican officials, who are to be sent by the President of the
                    Republic of Santo Domingo, to confer with Mr. Desiderio Arias on the north coast
                    of the republic. It is also requested that the commander of this vessel be
                    instructed to convey this commission back to Santo Domingo City after the
                    conference.</p>
                <p>Should Mr. Arias desire to proceed to Santo Domingo City it is also requested
                    that you authorize the commander of the vessel to accede to Mr. Arias’ wishes in
                    regard to such transportation.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
